  "created": "2025-10-08",
  "description": "The maltose regulon coordinates expression of five operons (malEFG, malK-lamB-malM, malPQ, malT, malI) involved in maltose and maltodextrin uptake and catabolism. The MalT activator integrates signals from maltose availability, catabolite repression (CRP-cAMP), and the MalK protein to coordinate transport, enzymatic processing, and regulatory gene expression across the genome.",
  "id": "ecoli_mal_regulon",
