    "and": 3,
    "not": 1,
    "or": 3
  },
  "mermaid": "graph TD\n    %% Input Signals\n    A[Maltose in Medium] --> B[Maltose Transport]\n    C[Maltodextrins in Medium] --> D[Maltodextrin Transport]\n    E[Glucose Status] --> F[cAMP Synthesis]\n    \n    %% Transport\n    B --> G[LamB Porin]\n    D --> G\n    G --> H[Maltose/Maltodextrin Inside]\n    H --> I[Maltotriose Formation]\n    \n    %% Decision: Maltose Present?\n    I --> J{Maltose/Maltotriose<br/>Present?}\n    \n    %% No Maltose - Basal State\n    J -->|No| K[MalT Inactive]\n    K --> L[Low mal Gene Expression]\n    L --> M[Basal Transport Only]\n    M --> N[No Maltose Catabolism]\n    \n    %% Maltose Present - MalT Activation\n    J -->|Yes| O[Maltotriose Binds MalT]\n    O --> P[MalT Conformational Change]\n    P --> Q[MalT Active Form]\n    \n    %% Decision: Glucose Status\n    F --> R{High cAMP?}\n    \n    %% AND Gate 1: CRP-cAMP Requirement\n    Q --> ANDGATE1{MalT Active AND<br/>CRP-cAMP Present?}\n    R -->|Yes| S[CRP-cAMP Complex]\n    S --> ANDGATE1\n    \n    %% MalK Regulatory Signal\n    T[MalK ATPase] --> U[ATP Binding]\n    U --> V[MalK-ATP Complex]\n    V --> W[MalK Regulatory State]\n    \n    %% AND Gate 2: MalK Anti-activation\n    ANDGATE1 -->|Yes| ANDGATE2{MalT-CRP Active AND<br/>MalK-ATP Low?}\n    W --> X{High MalK-ATP?}\n    X -->|No| ANDGATE2\n    \n    %% Full Activation\n    ANDGATE2 -->|Yes| Y[MalT Binds Mal Boxes]\n    Y --> Z[Multiple Operon Activation]\n    \n    %% malEFG Operon\n    Z --> AA[malEFG Transcription]\n    AA --> AB[MalE Periplasmic Binding Protein]\n    AB --> AC[MalF Membrane Protein]\n    AC --> AD[MalG Membrane Protein]\n    \n    %% malK-lamB-malM Operon\n    Z --> AE[malK-lamB-malM Transcription]\n    AE --> T\n    AE --> AF[LamB Maltose Porin]\n    AF --> G\n    AE --> AG[MalM Maltose Regulation]\n    \n    %% malPQ Operon\n    Z --> AH[malPQ Transcription]\n    AH --> AI[MalP Phosphorylase]\n    AI --> AJ[MalQ Amylomaltase]\n    \n    %% Maltose Catabolism\n    H --> AK[Maltose Substrate]\n    AI --> AL[Maltodextrin to Maltose + Glucose-1-P]\n    AK --> AL\n    AL --> AM[Maltose Hydrolysis]\n    AJ --> AN[Maltose to Glucose]\n    AM --> AN\n    AN --> AO[Glucose Products]\n    AO --> AP[Glycolysis Entry]\n    AP --> AQ[Energy Production]\n    \n    %% AND Gate 3: malT Autoactivation\n    Y --> ANDGATE3{MalT Active AND<br/>malT Promoter?}\n    Q --> ANDGATE3\n    ANDGATE3 -->|Yes| AR[malT Gene Transcription]\n    AR --> AS[More MalT Protein]\n    AS --> K\n    \n    %% Catabolite Repression Path\n    R -->|No| AT[Low cAMP]\n    AT --> AU[CRP Inactive]\n    AU --> AV[Weak mal Expression]\n    AV --> AW[Glucose Preference]\n    \n    %% MalK Inhibition Path\n    X -->|Yes| AX[/MalK-ATP Inhibits MalT/]\n    AX --> AY[Reduced mal Expression]\n    AY --> AZ[Feedback Control]\n    \n    %% System Outputs\n    N --> BA[Maltose System Off]\n    AQ --> BB[Maltose Utilization]\n    AW --> BC[Glucose-Preferential Growth]\n    AZ --> BD[Regulated Mal Expression]\n    \n    %% Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n    style A fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style B fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style C fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style D fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style E fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style F fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style G fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style H fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style I fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style J fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style K fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style L fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style M fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style N fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style O fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style P fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style Q fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style R fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style ANDGATE1 fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style S fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style T fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style U fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style V fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style W fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style ANDGATE2 fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style X fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style Y fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style Z fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AA fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AB fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style AC fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style AD fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style AE fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AF fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AG fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AH fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AI fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AJ fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AK fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AL fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AM fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AN fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AO fill:#000000,color:#fff\n    style AP fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AQ fill:#000000,color:#fff\n    style ANDGATE3 fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style AR fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AS fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style AT fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AU fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AV fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AW fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AX fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style AY fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AZ fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BA fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BB fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BC fill:#000000,color:#fff\n    style BD fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000",
  "name": "Maltose Regulon and Multi-Operon Coordination",
  "notGates": 1,
  "notes": "This flowchart represents the maltose regulon with 40 unique nodes (A-BD). Contains 2 OR logic gates (maltose presence, glucose status) and 3 AND gates (MalT activation requires maltose AND CRP-cAMP; full activation requires MalT-CRP AND low MalK-ATP; autoregulation requires MalT AND malT promoter). The system demonstrates multi-operon coordination, integration with catabolite repression, and ATP-dependent feedback control through MalK. Five operons are coordinately regulated by MalT binding to mal boxes. All mechanisms validated against genetic and biochemical studies.",
  "organism": "E. coli",
  "relatedProcesses": [
    "ecoli_lac_operon",
    "ecoli_ara_operon",
    "ecoli_catabolite_repression"
  ],
  "scientificAccuracy": "This flowchart is based on extensive research on the maltose system, one of the most thoroughly characterized multi-operon regulons. The MalT activation mechanism, CRP-cAMP integration, and ATP-dependent MalK regulatory function have been validated through genetic, biochemical, and structural studies. The maltose system serves as a model for understanding coordinated gene regulation.",
